directions/0/description: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
directions/1/description: In a bowl, mix the olive oil, Worcestershire sauce, turmeric, mustard, and garlic.
directions/2/description: Arrange the chicken breast halves in a medium baking dish, and top each with 2 halves bacon. Brush with the glaze.
directions/3/description: Cover, and bake 45 minutes in the preheated oven. Remove cover, and continue baking 15 minutes, or until chicken juices run clear.
name: Yellow Chicken
summary: Skinned chicken breasts topped with bacon and a mustard glaze.

directions/0/description: Make shallow crosswise slits in the meat of the chicken parts to help absorb more flavor. Mix together the lemon juice and meat tenderizer; rub into the chicken meat. Place chicken into a shallow dish.
directions/1/description: Place 1/2 cup yogurt, cumin, coriander, cilantro, paprika, turmeric, salt, pepper, and garlic into a blender or food processor, and blend until smooth. Transfer to a bowl, and stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of yogurt. Pour over the chicken parts, cover, and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 8 hours, or overnight.
directions/3/description: Lightly oil the grill grate. Remove chicken from the marinade, and discard any remaining marinade. Grill chicken 30 to 45 minutes, turning frequently to prevent burning, until juices run clear. Smaller pieces will finish cooking first.
name: Indian Barbeque Chicken
summary: Marinate the chicken overnight for a deliciously flavorful and tender chicken dish. This is an adaptation of Tandoori style chicken, minus the red coloring.

directions/0/description: Remove giblets from chicken cavity, rinse chicken inside and out.
directions/1/description: In a large stock pot or container, mix water, sage, celery seed, thyme, salt, sugar and soy sauce to create brine. Stir well until the sugar and salt are dissolved. Place the chicken in the brine, cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
directions/2/description: Remove chicken from the brine and rinse well inside and out. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of seasoned salt. Bake the chicken at 400 degrees F for 45 minutes.
name: Savory Chicken Brine
summary: Brining a chicken with soy sauce makes a juicier and more flavorful chicken. Great for baked, grilled or fried chicken.

directions/0/description: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
directions/1/description: In a large skillet brown the chicken in butter/margarine. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from skillet and place in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking dish.
directions/2/description: In the drippings (in the skillet), saute onion and celery until tender. Add cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce. Mix well.
directions/3/description: Pour cranberry mixture over chicken and bake in the preheated oven for 90 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
ingredients/0: 1 (2 to 3 pound) whole chicken, cut into pieces
name: Cranberry BBQ Chicken
summary: A very pretty chicken; you can use a whole chicken cut up, or pieces. I generally use Country Legs (thigh & drumstick) as that is the cheapest chicken available.

directions/0/description: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain.
directions/1/description: Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large, heavy frying pan over medium heat. Add pancetta and garlic; saute until brown and crisp, about 8 minutes. Remove from the heat and cool slightly.
directions/2/description: Whisk cream, Parmesan, egg yolks, basil, and parsley together in a large bowl until well blended.
directions/3/description: Stir chicken into the pancetta mixture until combined. Add cooked spaghetti and cream mixture. Toss over medium-low heat until chicken is heated through and sauce forms a thick coating over the spaghetti, about 4 minutes. Do not boil or the eggs will scramble. Season with salt and pepper and transfer to a large, wide serving bowl.
ingredients/8: ¼ cup chopped fresh Italian parsley
ingredients/10: salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
name: Chicken Carbonara
summary: This chicken carbonara is simply delicious!

directions/0/description: Place chicken breasts in a large resealable plastic freezer bag, one at a time. Lightly pound chicken breasts to an even thickness of about 3/4-inch. Combine oil, balsamic vinegar, garlic, Italian herb seasoning, salt and pepper in a small bowl and whisk until combined. Pour half of the marinade over the chicken, reseal bag, and set aside to marinate for at least 15 minutes. (Chicken and marinade can be prepared ahead; covered and refrigerated overnight.)
directions/1/description: Preheat grill to medium heat or about 350 degrees F. Combine remaining marinade with diced tomatoes and red onion; set aside. Transfer chicken from marinade onto grill surface and discard marinade. Grill chicken for 4 to 6 minutes per side or until cooked through. Transfer the chicken to a serving plate and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Spoon bruschetta mixture over chicken and top with basil; serve immediately.
ingredients/4: 1 tablespoon Spice Islands® Italian Herb Seasoning
ingredients/5: ½ teaspoon Spice Islands® Fine Grind Sea Salt
ingredients/6: ¼ teaspoon Spice Islands® Fine Grind Black Pepper
ingredients/9: ½ cup shredded Italian blend cheese
ingredients/10: ¼ cup finely chopped fresh basil
name: Bruschetta Chicken
summary: All the flavors of bruschetta on top of juicy grilled chicken!

directions/0/description: Place chicken in a large pot with onion, carrots, celery, and peppercorns; add water to cover by 1 inch. Cover the pot and bring to a boil; reduce heat to a gentle boil and cook until meat falls off the bone, about 90 minutes.
directions/1/description: Remove chicken from the pot and let sit until cool enough to handle. Shred or chop meat.
name: Boiled Chicken
summary: This boiled chicken recipe is a wonderful basic recipe for many uses. Boiled chicken meat is called for in many other recipes.

directions/0/description: Heat olive oil in a large soup pot over medium to medium-high heat. Saute onion, carrots, and celery until they begin to become tender and caramelize, about 10 minutes. Add garlic and saute for 1 minute. Season vegetables with a generous sprinkling of salt and pepper while cooking.
directions/1/description: Stir in butter to melt; stir flour into the veggies and butter until evenly distributed and veggies are coated. Pour in broth and milk, stirring until well combined. Turn the heat up and bring the mixture to a simmer. Add thyme, salt, pepper, and turmeric. Stir in peas and corn. Stir in chicken to combine and allow to simmer, 10 to 15 minutes. Taste and adjust seasonings before serving.
ingredients/5: salt and ground black pepper to taste
ingredients/11: 1 teaspoon salt, or more to taste
ingredients/12: ½ teaspoon ground black pepper, or more to taste
name: Homemade Chicken Stew
summary: A hearty, creamy chicken stew, chock-full of veggies and tender bites of chicken!

directions/0/description: In a cup or small bowl, stir together the Italian seasoning, onion powder and garlic powder. Sprinkle over both sides of the chicken. Place 1 tablespoon of cream cheese on the center of each piece, and spread slightly. Tuck in the sides, and roll up tightly. Secure with toothpicks.
directions/1/description: Place the bread crumbs on a plate or in a shallow bowl. Roll the chicken rolls in the bread crumbs to coat. Place on a plate, cover, and freeze for about 30 minutes.
directions/2/description: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
directions/3/description: Heat the butter and oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Brown the chicken rolls on all sides, this should take about 5 minutes. Transfer the rolls to a baking dish.
directions/4/description: Bake for 20 minutes in the preheated oven, or until chicken is no longer pink and the juices run clear. Spoon drippings from the dish over the rolls before serving.
ingredients/3: 4 skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - pounded to 1/4 inch thickness
ingredients/4: 4 tablespoons garlic flavored cream cheese spread
ingredients/5: ¼ cup garlic and herb seasoned dry bread crumbs
name: Chicken Nepiev
summary: Chicken, cream cheese, and garlic unite in this marriage of Chicken Neptune, Chicken Kiev, and a shorthanded pantry! Takes less fuss than either of its inspirations, and recipe can easily be increased for larger households.

directions/0/description: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a baking dish with cooking spray.
directions/1/description: Mix together artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, and garlic pepper in a medium bowl. Place chicken in the prepared baking dish; cover chicken evenly with artichoke mixture.
directions/2/description: Bake, uncovered, in the preheated oven until chicken is no longer pink in the center and juices run clear, about 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).
ingredients/1: 1 (15 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped
name: Artichoke Chicken
summary: This artichoke chicken is the most flavorful chicken you will ever have in your life. It melts in your mouth and is to die for!

directions/0/description: Season the chicken breasts on both sides with salt and pepper. Place the flour, egg and panko crumbs into separate shallow dishes. Coat the chicken breasts in flour, shaking off any excess. Dip them into the egg, and then press into the panko crumbs until well coated on both sides.
directions/1/description: Heat 1/4 inch of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place chicken in the hot oil, and cook 3 or 4 minutes per side, or until golden brown.
ingredients/0: 4 skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - pounded to 1/2 inch thickness
ingredients/5: 1 cup oil for frying, or as needed
name: Chicken Katsu
summary: This is my family recipe for Chicken Katsu - Japanese style fried chicken. Can also be used to make Tonkatsu, just use pork cutlets instead of chicken. Serve with white rice and tonkatsu sauce.
